'''Jason Marsden''' (born [[January 3]], [[1975]]) is an [[Wikipedia:United States|American]] voice actor who voiced [[Rosh Penin]] in ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy]]'' and numerous characters in the ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'' series such as [[Dustil Onasi]] and [[Brejik]].

Marsden is most recognized as the voice of [[Wikipedia:Max Goof|Max Goof]], son of classic Disney character [[Wikipedia:Goofy|Goofy]], in the 1995 animated film [[Wikipedia: A Goofy Movie|''A Goofy Movie'']] in addition to the majority of post-[[1995]] appearances of the Max Goof character, as well as the voice of Haku in the English-dubbed version of the 2001 Japanese animated film [[Wikipedia:Spirited Away|''Spirited Away'']].

He is also known for his roles in the [[W:c:fallout:Fallout series|''Fallout'']] of video games - [[W:c:fallout:Myron|Myron]] in [[W:c:fallout:Fallout 2|''Fallout 2'']], [[W:c:fallout:Horus|Horus]] in [[W:c:fallout:Fallout Tactics|''Fallout Tactics'']] and [[W:c:fallout:Craig Boone|Craig Boone]] in [[W:c:fallout:Fallout: New Vegas|''Fallout: New Vegas'']].

